<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="800" d:DesignHeight="450"
             x:Class="StellarMVVM_2024.Views.making_decisions_archive_screen">
	<UserControl.Styles>
		<StyleInclude Source="/Styles/archive info styles/making_decisions_archive_stylesheet.axaml"/>
	</UserControl.Styles>
	<Panel Background="Pink">
		<StackPanel
			HorizontalAlignment="Center"
			Name="makingDecisionsArchive">
			<TextBlock
				Classes="title"
				PointerReleased="returnPrevious">
				making decisions
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				1. always consider your assets (what you have) and liabilities (what you owe)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				2. consider if something is in your standard of living? is it a luxury or a necessity?
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				3. if you are considering a loan, look at the interest rate and time to repay the loan
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				4. for housing, consider an apartment (flexible if you want to move) and a house (flexible for customization)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				5. for cars, remember that a car instantly depreciates at first use
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				6. for insurance, look at the benefits. look at the annual payment. APR? copayments?
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				7. always remember to have multiple plans. think of the pros and cons.
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				8. ensure you can maintain whatever you buy. house/car maintenance, premiums, etc.
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				9. consider the financial aids, like for tuitions, FAFSA can help. deductibles exist, exemptions, etc.
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				10. research thoroughly for alternatives.
			</TextBlock>
		</StackPanel>
	</Panel>
</UserControl>
